message: Focus on cutting soft items (both natural and artificial) as they reliably yield 25 points. Framing a single cut item almost always boosts its value to 45. Combining *two* similar soft items (e.g., artificial+soft with artificial+soft) before cutting and then framing can yield even higher values (e.g., 70). Avoid combining more than two items or mixing too many different features, especially 'hard' ones, as this often leads to 'overcomplicated' items with negative values. Always frame last.
